ier and potential safe haven investment etf securities is a global pioneer in exchange traded products etps having developed the worlds first gold etp in  silver remains cheap relative to gold with the goldtosilver price ratio at the highest since  as of february   the goldtosilver ratio rose to the highest level since the global financial crisis silver is cheaper compared to gold at this stage and should its historic correlation with gold reestablish itself there appears to be catchup potential for the metal with silver being a byproduct of mining for other metals and mining activity paring back we believe silver is likely to enter another year of supply deficit platinum and palladium benefit from rising wealth in emerging markets rapidly increasing emerging market lifestyles percapita gross domestic product gdp and coincident auto sales together with tightening global emission standards are causing a structural shift in the demand for platinum and palladium while investors are familiar with gold and its investment benefits and silver with its more industrial demand focus less well known are platinum and palladium the majority of the demand for platinum and palladium is industrial for emissions controls through the use of catalytic converters a key advantage platinum and palladium have over other bulk industrial metals are the low storage costs associated with precious metals why invest in precious metal etfs costeffective accessible transparent simple precious metal etfs offer a cost efficient way to participate in the gold silver platinum and palladium bullion market without having to take physical delivery of the gold itself etfs can be bought and sold whenever the stock exchange is open as prices are quoted throughout the day unlike other investment vehicles etf constituents are published on a daily basis this transparency makes it easier for the investor to see exactly what they own etfs are listed and trade in a similar way as shares through the same brokers and platforms why invest in a basket of precious metal etfs precious metals pms are classified as currencies when referenced in this piece a ‘basket’ of precious metals includes gold silver platinum and palladium we believe that a precious metals basket is an attractive alternative to holding a broad based commodity benchmark the precious metals basket has a history of outperforming the bloomberg commodity index bcom and sp  index a precious metals basket is a potential attractive addition to most portfolios compared to traditional broad commodity exposure etf securities is the only us firm to offer a basket of precious metals in an etf wrapper etf securities precious metal etf offerings productexchange codecusipmerfactsheetprospectus etfs physical palladium shares pall a      etfs physical platinum shares pplt v      etfs physical precious metals basket shares gltr w      etfs physical silver shares sivr x      etfs physical swiss gold shares sgol y      brexit is an abbreviation of british exit that mirrors the term grexit it refers to the possibility that britain will withdraw from the european union etf securities listed the world’s first gold exchangetraded commodity in  sp  index  an index of  stocks chosen for market size liquidity and industry grouping among other factors the sp  is designed to be a leading indicator of us equities and is meant to reflect the riskreturn characteristics of the large cap universe bloomberg commodity index  a broadly diversified commodity price index that tracks prices of futures contracts on physical commodities on the commodity markets careers cookies and privacy policy terms  conditions documents etf securities copyright  please call etfsbuy    or click here to access a prospectus online investing involves risk including possible loss of principal etf shares are bought and sold at market price not nav and are not individually redeemed from the fund investors buy and sell shares on a secondary market ie not directly from the 